Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp\n+++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp\n@@ -2129,7 +2129,11 @@\n     }\n-    StartIdx0 = Builder.CreateTrunc(StartIdx0, IntStepTy);\n+    // Only truncate if types differ to avoid invalid constant expression casts.\n+    if (StartIdx0->getType() != IntStepTy) {\n+      StartIdx0 = Builder.CreateTrunc(StartIdx0, IntStepTy);\n+    }\n'}`
responded: Here is the patch to fix the bug by adding a type check before calling `CreateTrunc` in `VPScalarIVStepsRecipe::execute`:

```diff
--- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp
+++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp
@@ -2129,7 +2129,11 @@
     }
-    StartIdx0 = Builder.CreateTrunc(StartIdx0, IntStepTy);
+    // Only truncate if types differ to avoid invalid constant expression casts.
+    if (StartIdx0->getType() != IntStepTy) {
+      StartIdx0 = Builder.CreateTrunc(StartIdx0, IntStepTy);
+    }
```

This ensures that truncation is only performed when necessary, preventing invalid cast assertions.

